    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you are experiencing a classic \"goblin\" back issue, where the weight is being lifted by your spine rather than your strong legs and glutes. This often happens when your hips are too low or your feet are too far apart, causing your back to round out of fear. To fix this, try keeping your hips high and your chest proud, while ensuring your feet are shoulder-width apart so you can push through the ground more effectively. If you still feel pain, consider reducing the weight and focusing on perfecting your technique before adding more load.",
