      "content": "I apologize for the confusion; that was definitely not the right term, and I am sorry I introduced unnecessary confusion. When you feel that strain in your lower back during a deadlift, it usually means your spine isn't staying rigid enough, or your hips are dropping too low before you start the lift. To correct this, focus on keeping your back flat against the floor like a flatbed truck, and engage your glutes and hamstrings to drive the weight up rather than pulling it with your back. If the pain persists, it is best to take a break and consult a trainer or physical therapist to ensure your form is safe.",
